  2.3 What shapes those decisions before the LLM ever sees the turn

  Three-tier system prompt (system_prompt.py:62-403), cached once per session, rebuilt only on compression:

  - Stable tier — identity (SOUL.md), tool-behavior guidance (memory/session_search/skills/kanban only if those tools are present), model-family operational rules (Google vs OpenAI/Codex), skills index, env hints,
  coding-posture blocks (coding_context.coding_system_blocks())
  - Context tier — system_message + AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md/.cursorrules from CWD, all threat-scanned before injection (prompt_builder.py:45-61)
  - Volatile tier — built-in memory, USER.md, external memory snapshot, timestamp (date-only for byte-stability)

  invalidate_system_prompt() (system_prompt.py:406) is the only path that rebuilds the cache.

  2.4 What shapes the tool surface the LLM sees

  The LLM is shown a deliberately curated set, not the full inventory. Pipeline at model_tools.py:272-536:

  1. Toolset resolution — enabled minus disabled (subtract-last for strict removal)
  2. check_fn() probes (30s TTL) — Docker/Modal/env-var availability
  3. Dynamic schema rewrites — execute_code, discord, browser_navigate are re-described to mention only available companions, so the model cannot hallucinate calls to missing tools
  4. Tool-search activation (tools/tool_search.py:234) — when deferrable MCP/plugin tools exceed threshold_pct * context (default 10%), they are physically removed from the schema and replaced by 3 bridge tools (tool_search,
  tool_describe, tool_call)
  5. Schema sanitization — llama.cpp/Kimi-compatible shape fixes
  6. Skills index injected into system prompt — filtered by platform, disabled list, required tools/toolsets; "compact categories" demoted (names kept, descriptions dropped) under coding-focus posture

  This is the single most important decision-shaping mechanism: if a tool isn't here, the model literally cannot pick it.

  2.5 Compression heuristic (the only "what to forget" decision)

  context_compressor.py:

  - Preflight (turn_context.py:248-314) — rough estimate before API call; loops ≤3 passes; skips if last real usage was below the estimate (should_defer_preflight_to_real_usage)
  - Post-turn (conversation_loop.py:3815) — fires when real prompt_tokens >= threshold_tokens (default 75%)
  - Algorithm: prune old tool results → strip pre-last-image multimodal → preserve first 3 + budget-protected tail → LLM-summarize middle → iteratively merge prior summary
  - Budget: min 2000 / ratio 20% / ceiling 12000 tokens
  - Summary prefix explicitly tells the model: treat as reference, latest user message always wins, do not resume stale tasks

  2.6 Retry / recovery ladder (per API call)

  Strict order in conversation_loop.py:811+. Each is one-shot per iteration via TurnRetryState:

  1. Nous rate-limit guard (cross-session breaker)
  2. API call attempt + pre_api_request hook
  3. Auth refresh — Nous OAuth, Anthropic OAuth, Copilot, xAI Codex
  4. Billing/entitlement refresh on 401
  5. Credential-pool rotation on 429
  6. Image shrink on size errors
  7. Multimodal tool-content downgrade for strict providers
  8. Disable 1M-context beta on 403
  9. Strip reasoning_details on thinking-signature 400
  10. Long-context tier reduction (Anthropic 1M→200K) on 429
  11. Activate fallback provider (rate-limit + billing)
  12. Compress 1–3× on 413/overflow
  13. Jittered exponential backoff (5s base, 120s cap)

  Terminal failures bubble up with classification from error_classifier.py.

  2.7 The action-gating cascade (tool execution → actually running)

  A tool call passes through 7 gates before any side effect (assembled from model_tools.py:922-1139 and tools/approval.py):

  [1] Tool-search bridge unwrap + scope check        model_tools.py:933
  [2] Tool request middleware (arg rewrite)          model_tools.py:1000
  [3] pre_tool_call plugin hook (may block)          model_tools.py:1031
  [4] ACP/Zed edit approval (IDE-only)               model_tools.py:1070
  [5] Terminal-only command-approval cascade:        tools/approval.py
      [5a] Hardline block — UNCONDITIONAL                  L1060
           rm -rf /, mkfs, dd of=/dev/sd*, shutdown,
           kill -1, fork bomb. No bypass exists.
      [5b] YOLO bypass (frozen env var)                    L1067
      [5c] Dangerous-pattern detection (47 regexes)        L1070
      [5d] Session-scoped allowlist check                  L1075
      [5e] Approval-mode router                            L1102
           CLI → interactive [once/session/always/deny]
           Gateway → /approve|/deny over async queue
           Cron → respects approvals.cron_mode
      [5f] Smart approval — aux LLM verdict                L1382
           APPROVE | DENY | ESCALATE (overrides patterns)
      [5g] Tirith security scan (subprocess)         tools/tirith_security.py
           Homograph URLs, terminal injection, ANSI escapes
  [6] Execution middleware (metrics, final checks)   model_tools.py:1129
  [7] TOOL RUNS
      └─ Post-exec: checkpoint (pre-mutation), output truncation,
         per-turn 200KB spill, tool_guardrails loop detection

  Key invariants:
  - Hardline block is unbypassable — even YOLO, even cron approve-mode.
  - Tirith findings + pattern findings are merged into a single approval request — so a gateway force=True reply can't bypass one because only the other was shown.
  - Checkpoints fire before mutation, not after. Rollback is always available.
  - Interrupts are per-thread, not per-process. Parallel sessions don't interfere.

  2.8 Loop guardrails (agent/tool_guardrails.py:224-375)

  Behavioral safety net the agent imposes on itself:

  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                      Pattern                      │                      Action                      │
  ├───────────────────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Identical (tool + args) failing N times           │ hard stop (if hard_stop_enabled)                 │
  ├───────────────────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Same tool failing N times (any args)              │ warning appended to result                       │
  ├───────────────────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Read-only tool returning identical result N times │ warning suggesting use of result or query change │
  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  2.9 Skill curation (long-horizon behavior shaping)

  agent/curator.py:255-310 — runs every interval_hours (7d default) when agent is idle > min_idle_hours (2h):

  - State machine: active → stale (30d unused) → archived (90d unused)
  - First-run deferred a full interval so a fresh install doesn't archive built-ins
  - PROTECTED_BUILTIN_SKILLS = {"plan"} (skill_usage.py:66) — never archived even with prune_builtins: true
  - Pinned + hub-installed + bundled-manifest skills bypass all transitions
  - LLM review pass (curator.py:344) consolidates narrow sibling skills under umbrella names — never deletes, only archives

