  3. Notable / surprising decisions

  1. Grace call — after budget hits zero, one final API call is granted (conversation_loop.py:480). If that still returns no final text, a toolless summary request is fired that doesn't consume budget at all.
  2. System prompt rebuilds only on compression — the date-only timestamp in volatile tier keeps it byte-stable across an entire calendar day so prefix-cache holds.
  3. Subdirectory hints are appended to tool results, not the system prompt — so cwd discovery never invalidates the cache.
  4. Smart approval is an LLM-driven escape valve — pattern matching is just the first stage. An auxiliary LLM can override pattern findings, catching false positives like python -c "print('hi')".
  5. Tool descriptions are rewritten if their referenced companions are unavailable — prevents a class of hallucinated tool calls that other agent frameworks suffer from.
  6. Tool-search activation is a context budget decision, not a discovery feature — core tools are never deferred; only MCP/plugin tools are hidden when they'd eat >10% of context.
  7. Compression summary is explicitly demoted with SUMMARY_PREFIX — instructs the model to never resume stale work from the summary; latest user msg always wins. The compressor also recognizes and strips its own past prefix
  versions to prevent re-compression drift.
  8. Checkpoints use shared shadow-git (GIT_DIR/GIT_WORK_TREE/GIT_INDEX_FILE) so the user's .git never sees agent commits. Pre-mutation, not post.

  ---
  4. One-paragraph executive summary

  The agent runs a single run_conversation() loop (agent/conversation_loop.py:371) that, on each iteration, calls a provider with a cached three-tier system prompt, then routes the response into one of five branches: execute
  tool calls, return text, length-continue, recover from empty, or hard-exit. Tool visibility is curated in model_tools.get_tool_definitions() — toolsets are intersected, availability is probed, descriptions are rewritten to
  remove references to absent tools, and large MCP/plugin surfaces are hidden behind a tool_search bridge when they would consume >10% of context. Every tool execution passes a 7-gate cascade (scope, middleware, plugin block,
  IDE approval, command approval cascade with hardline block + smart LLM verdict, tirith scan, execution middleware), then post-exec checkpoint + truncation + loop guardrails contain its effects. Context is preserved with an
  LLM-driven 75%-threshold compressor that explicitly demotes past summaries so the model never resumes stale tasks. Memory, coding posture, and skill curation operate around this loop as out-of-band shapers — they change what
   the agent knows and reaches for, but the loop's decision policy itself lives entirely in conversation_loop.py.